- **Address:** ⚠️ Not Available  

**Emergency Steps:**  
- Keep a flashlight and batteries handy in case of a power outage.  
- Unplug sensitive electronic equipment to protect against power surges when the power returns.  
- Keep refrigerator and freezer doors closed to maintain the cold temperature as long as possible.  
- Have a backup charging method for your phone and keep hard copies of emergency numbers.  
- Sign up for ZIP code alerts from PG&E to stay informed about power outages in your area by texting “ENROLL” to 97633.

**Non-Emergency Tips:**  
- For billing inquiries or assistance, visit the [SJCE website](https://www.sanjoseca.gov/your-government/departments-offices/energy) for support options.  
- Consider enrolling in programs that offer 100% renewable energy to reduce your carbon footprint.  
- Regularly check the SJCE website for updates on service status and community programs.